use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zmh1665702705308.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zmh1665702705308.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zmh1665702705308.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zmh1665702705308\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      lock isolation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__lock_isolation_145343\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the isolation level for the database transactions of the connector.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__topic_d47777e1_d47778e1_d47779e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__d6501e17\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$Mnemonic_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n                          lock isolation\n                          <code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Level</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__d6501e32\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$Mnemonic_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n                          iso\n                          <code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Level</var>\n</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__d6501e47\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Valid values for <var class=\"keyword varname\">Level</var> depend on the DBMS\n        connector.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__topic_d31232e1_d31233e1_d31234e1_d31235e1_d31236e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042688e92\">\n                        \n Valid Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__p_d47789e1_d47790e1_d47791e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Level</var> is one of the following:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Valid Values per Connector</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n Long Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n Short Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n Applies To\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">repeatable read</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">rr</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">\n Highest level of isolation; has the most overhead and is the safest.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n DB2, MSS, MQL, PGS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">read stability</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">rs</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">Equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">repeatable read</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n DB2, PGS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">serializable</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">sl</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">Equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">repeatable read</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n DB2, MSS, MQL, PGS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">read committed</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">rc</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">\n Medium level of isolation.\n <p class=\"p\">Default level for all connectors except DB2, which is <code class=\"ph codeph\">cursor stability</code>.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n MSS, MQL, PGS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">cursor stability</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">cs</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">Equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">read committed</code>.\n                     Default for DB2. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n DB2\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">read uncommitted</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ru</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">\n Lowest level of isolation; has the least overhead, but is considered unsafe regarding data consistency.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n MSS, MQL, PGS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">uncommitted read</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ur</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">Equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">read\n                     uncommitted</code>. </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n DB2\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">statement level snapshot</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ss</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">Usable only if you also set the\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">read_committed_snapshot</code> in the database to\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>. To do so, execute the following script:\n                     <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">alter database MYDATABASE\nset read_committed_snapshot on\nwith &lt;termination&gt;</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n MSS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">transaction level snapshot</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ts</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__3\">Usable only if you set the\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">allow_snapshot_isolation</code> in the database to\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>. To do so, execute the following script:\n                     <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">alter database MYDATABASE\nset allow_snapshot_isolation on</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4502e1_d4503e1_d4504e1__entry__4\">\n MSS\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__note_w2890ab1b5b5b7_w2891ab1b5b5_w2892ab1b5_w2893ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> These names of these levels are\n         defined by the SQL-92 standard. However, the names employed by different databases do not\n         always correspond to these names. For example, DB2 defines <code class=\"ph codeph\">repeatable read</code>\n         as <code class=\"ph codeph\">serializable</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">read stability</code> as <code class=\"ph codeph\">repeatable\n            read</code>. Consult your database documentation for the terminology used by your\n         database.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__topic_d31237e1_d31238e1_d31239e1_d31240e1_d31241e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042688e438\">\n                        \n Use\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__1\">\n Applies to\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__2\">\n Mnemonic\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__3\">\n Connector Syntax\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__1\">\n DB2\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__2\">\n DB2\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__3\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$DB2_PARAMS</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__1\">\n Microsoft SQL Server connector\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__2\">\n MSS\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__3\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$MSS_PARAMS</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__1\">\n MySQL connector\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__2\">\n MQL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__3\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$MQL_PARAMS</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__1\">\n PostgreSQL connector\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__2\">\n PGS\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zmh1665702705308__table_d4505e1_d4506e1_d4507e1__entry__3\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$PGS_PARAM</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__topic_d31242e1_d31243e1_d31244e1_d31245e1_d31246e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1042688e534\">\n                        \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zmh1665702705308__p_d47798e1_d47799e1_d47800e1\">A higher isolation level reduces the types of concurrency effects that users may encounter, but requires more system resources and increases the chances that one transaction will block another.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iio1665702704280.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Locking Support on DB2</a><p>Full Uniface locking support (optimistic, cautious, and paranoid) is available.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fug1665702705112.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>default locking</a><p>Set the default locking strategy employed by Uniface.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/npx1665702705652.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>update isolation</a><p>Specify an isolation level to be used specifically by the lock ProcScript statement.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534511\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534511\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "lock isolation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 lock isolation Set the isolation level for the database transactions of the connector. USYS$Mnemonic_PARAMS = lock isolation : Level USYS$Mnemonic_PARAMS = iso : Level Note: Valid values for Level depend on the DBMS connector. Valid Values Level is one of the following: Table 1. Valid Values per Connector Long Value Short Value Meaning Applies To repeatable read rr Highest level of isolation; has the most overhead and is the safest. DB2, MSS, MQL, PGS read stability rs Equivalent to repeatable read . DB2, PGS serializable sl Equivalent to repeatable read . DB2, MSS, MQL, PGS read committed rc Medium level of isolation. Default level for all connectors except DB2, which is cursor stability . MSS, MQL, PGS cursor stability cs Equivalent to read committed . Default for DB2. DB2 read uncommitted ru Lowest level of isolation; has the least overhead, but is considered unsafe regarding data consistency. MSS, MQL, PGS uncommitted read ur Equivalent to read uncommitted . DB2 statement level snapshot ss Usable only if you also set the read_committed_snapshot in the database to on . To do so, execute the following script: alter database MYDATABASE set read_committed_snapshot on with <termination> Copy MSS transaction level snapshot ts Usable only if you set the allow_snapshot_isolation in the database to on . To do so, execute the following script: alter database MYDATABASE set allow_snapshot_isolation on Copy MSS CAUTION: These names of these levels are defined by the SQL-92 standard. However, the names employed by different databases do not always correspond to these names. For example, DB2 defines repeatable read as serializable and read stability as repeatable read . Consult your database documentation for the terminology used by your database. Use Applies to Mnemonic Connector Syntax DB2 DB2 USYS$DB2_PARAMS Microsoft SQL Server connector MSS USYS$MSS_PARAMS MySQL connector MQL USYS$MQL_PARAMS PostgreSQL connector PGS USYS$PGS_PARAM Description A higher isolation level reduces the types of concurrency effects that users may encounter, but requires more system resources and increases the chances that one transaction will block another. Related Links Locking Support on DB2 Full Uniface locking support (optimistic, cautious, and paranoid) is available. default locking Set the default locking strategy employed by Uniface. update isolation Specify an isolation level to be used specifically by the lock ProcScript statement. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}